                    <div id="bio-text" class="about-text">
                        <p>I grew up in rural Putney, Vermont, with my parents, older sister, and cat. I did a lot of playing, drawing, and cross-country skiing.
                        I went to highschool as a day student at Northfield Mount Hermon in Western Massachusetts,
                        where I continued to spend a lot of time playing. I was the captain of the cross-country ski team, and competed in varsity crew, track, and
                        lacrosse.</p>
                        <br/>
                        <p>Currently, I'm taking a gap year before attending college. Some of my more exciting adventures have been two week-long Cuba peregrinations, a few weeks
                        of living in my car and working as a landscaper in Nantucket,
                        a 70ish day journey through Chile and Bolivia, where I spent something like half my time working at two hostels (one in Pucon and another in Santiago), and 
                        the long process of learning to build websites. At the moment, I'm working as a lift operator at Crested Butte Mountain Resort in Colorado, where I've learned that I love
                        freestyle skiing as much as I love backcountry skiing.</p>
                        <br/>
                        <p>Some of my more defining characteristics are my intensity, independence, intellectual curiousity, ambition,
                        intolerance of bullshit and hypocrisy, creativity, adventurousness, sociability, impatience, obsessiveness, and hubris.</p> 
                        <br/>
                        <p>While I am still very much a student, my primary professional skills are web development/design and analytical/persuasive writing.
                        In the future, I hope to apply information technology solutions to problems surrounding environmental conservation and the health of our civilization.</p>
