                    <div id="values-text" class="about-text">
                        <h5>I believe that curiousity is fundamentally good, that the natural world is sacred, and that individuals' decisions 
                        impact the quality of the future.</h5> 
                        <br/>
                        <p>I believe that people should only work towards goals which align with their values, and that the only reason to collaborate
                        is to work towards common goals. Therefore, shared values should be the foundation of any working relationship. It is a flaw of our
                        tech-era collaborative tools (and indeed capitalist collaboration in general) that everybody shares what they can do, but not why 
                        they want to do those things. I will address this problem here.</p>
                        <br/>
                        <p><b>I care about conserving the natural beauty of our world,</b> which I believe to be an elementary ingredient of human health and joy.
                        <br><br><b>I believe that intellectual curiousity is the noblest human craving,</b> and a natural consequence of the decision to appreciate life.
                        Extending this, I think that education is the single most important social system.
